From these examples, we see that the leading term in the numerator of \(\tan nx\) is \(n \tan x\). Extending this pattern to \(n = 2023\), the leading term in the numerator of \(\tan 2023x\) is \(2023 \tan x\). Since the coefficient \(a_{2023}\) corresponds to the leading term, we conclude that \(a_{2023} = 2023\). Thus, the final answer is \(\boxed{2023}\).
